{"title_page": "The Consumer Movement", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=November 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox book\n<!-- |italic title = (see above) -->\n| name             = The Consumer Movement\n| image            = \n| caption          = \n| author           = Helen Sorenson\n| title_orig       = \n| translator       = \n| illustrator      = \n| cover_artist     = \n| country          = United States\n| language         = \n| series           = \n| subject          = [[consumer movement]]\n| genre            = \n| publisher        = [[Harper (publisher)|Harper and Brothers]]\n| pub_date         = 1941\n| english_pub_date = \n| media_type       = \n| pages            = 245\n| isbn             = \n| oclc             = \n| dewey            = \n| congress         = \n| preceded_by      = \n| followed_by      = \n}}\n\n'''''The Consumer Movement''''' is a 1941 book on the [[consumer movement]] by Helen Sorenson.\n\n==Reviews==\nOne reviewer said that the book describes the consumer movement by describing what contemporary consumer organizations are doing as activism.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Hoyt|first1=Elizabeth E.|title=Reviewed Work: The Consumer Movement: What It Is and What It Means by Helen Sorenson|journal=The American Economic Review|date=September 1941|volume=31|issue=3|pages=673\u2013675|jstor=1805871|publisher=American Economic Association}}</ref>\n\nA reviewer for ''[[Kirkus Reviews]]'' said that the book describes \"consumer group organization, the variety of interests that constitute the consumer movement, the definite objectives of consumer groups, the spread of services, testing agencies, committees, leagues, associations of all kinds and their power as consumer groups\".<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/helen-sorenson/the-consumer-movement/ |title=THE CONSUMER MOVEMENT by Helen Sorenson |author=staff |work=[[Kirkus Reviews]] |date=1 March 1941 |accessdate=10 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Consumer Movement}}\n[[Category:1941 non-fiction books]]\n[[Category:Non-fiction books about consumerism]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=November 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox book\n<!-- |italic title = (see above) -->\n| name             = The Consumer Movement\n| image            = \n| caption          = \n| author           = Helen Sorenson\n| title_orig       = \n| translator       = \n| illustrator      = \n| cover_artist     = \n| country          = United States\n| language         = \n| series           = \n| subject          = [[consumer movement]]\n| genre            = \n| publisher        = [[Harper (publisher)|Harper and Brothers]]\n| pub_date         = 1941\n| english_pub_date = \n| media_type       = \n| pages            = 245\n| isbn             = \n| oclc             = \n| dewey            = \n| congress         = \n| preceded_by      = \n| followed_by      = \n}}\n\n'''''The Consumer Movement''''' is a 1941 book on the [[consumer movement]] by Helen Sorenson.\n\n==Reviews==\nOne reviewer said that the book describes the consumer movement by describing what contemporary consumer organizations are doing as activism.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Hoyt|first1=Elizabeth E.|title=Reviewed Work: The Consumer Movement: What It Is and What It Means by Helen Sorenson|journal=The American Economic Review|date=September 1941|volume=31|issue=3|pages=673\u2013675|jstor=1805871|publisher=American Economic Association}}</ref>\n\nA reviewer for ''[[Kirkus Reviews]]'' said that the book describes \"consumer group organization, the variety of interests that constitute the consumer movement, the definite objectives of consumer groups, the spread of services, testing agencies, committees, leagues, associations of all kinds and their power as consumer groups\".<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/helen-sorenson/the-consumer-movement/ |title=THE CONSUMER MOVEMENT by Helen Sorenson |author=staff |work=[[Kirkus Reviews]] |date=1 March 1941 |accessdate=10 June 2015}}</re